		<div id="content">
			<p class="contentText collegeText">Marianopolis College is an English-language private CEGEP currently located in Westmount, Quebec, Canada, and is one of the smallest Anglophone colleges of the province, giving students the personal attention they need to succeed.</p> 
			<p class="contentText collegeText">Recognized as one of Quebec&#39;s top pre-university colleges, Marianopolis College boasts a diverse student body comprised of 2,000 students from over 175 public and private high schools, English and French, from Quebec and abroad.</p>
			<p class="contentText collegeText">From early admission to Harvard University to direct entry to McGill University&#39;s Faculty of Law, Marianopolis College&#39;s students gain entry to the world&#39;s top universities every year.</p>
			<p class="contentText collegeText">It is also the only college in Quebec that offers five distinct special certificates, which allow students to touch upon other interests outside their curriculum: Environmental Studies, International Studies, Law and Social Justice, Native Studies and Third World Studies. </p>

			<h2>Student Life</h1>

			<p class="contentText collegeText">Student life at Marianopolis is supported by Congress, the student government, which organizes a variety of events and activities such as Halloween, Christmas, Earth Week, Valentine&#39;s Day, etc. The College has currently up to 100 student clubs and several athletic teams involved in competitive sports such as volleyball, badminton, dragon boat, etc. Marianopolis also offers a gymnasium and fitness center for students during the week. </p>
			<p class="contentText collegeText">Marianopolis is also the only college to hold a universal lunch break, called Activity Period, twice a week. This common break is an opportunity for students to hear from world-renowned guest speakers, play intramural sports, participate in clubs activities and socialize with peers outside of class. </p>
			<p class="contentText collegeText">Students also have the opportunity to get involved in a variety of enriching extracurricular activities, from the annual ArtsFest and the Christmas Fair Trade Bazaar, to creative writing, math and robotics competitions.</p>

			<h2>Why Marianopolis?</h1>
			<p class="contentText collegeText">Marianopolis is the place for motivated young people to achieve, grow and succeed. As Quebec&#39;s only English-language private college, Marianopolis has been uniquely positioned for more than a century to offer unparalleled support to students from various backgrounds. The college also provides exceptional resources and services to students in the classroom and beyond to guarantee a most empowering academic experience. At Marianopolis, students are challenged and prepared to take on the final step, university. </p>
